	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />When they say i386 in that message, they mean &quot;i386 and all binary-compatible extensions thereof&quot;, that is, i686 as opposed to amd64 which is not compatible. Canonical wants to entirely relegate 32-bit support in Ubuntu Desktop and Ubuntu Server to containers rather than the main repository within the next few years. Some of the endorsed but not fully Canonical-supported remixes, especially Xubuntu and Lubuntu, may retain 32-bit support longer, as their explicit goal includes repurposing PC hardware that can no longer run modern Windows well. And Xubuntu has never had the shopping lens crap.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


